Sethe, the protagonist ofBeloved,is a proud and independent woman who is extremely devoted to her children. Though she barely knew her own mother, Setheâ€™s motherly instincts are her most striking characteristic. Unwilling to relinquish her children to the physical, emotional, sexual, and spiritual trauma she endured as a slave at Sweet Home, she attempts to murder them in an act of motherly love and protection. She remains haunted by this and other scarring events in her past, which she tries, in vain, to repress.Read anin-depth analysis of Sethe.